applianceModeSupport.description: Whether Appliance Mode support is enabled. Valid values: `disable`, `enable`.

dnsSupport.description: Whether DNS support is enabled. Valid values: `disable`, `enable`.

ipv6Support.description: Whether IPv6 support is enabled. Valid values: `disable`, `enable`.

tags.description: Key-value tags for the EC2 Transit Gateway VPC Attachment. If configured with a provider `default_tags` configuration block present, tags with matching keys will overwrite those defined at the provider-level.

tagsAll.description: A map of tags assigned to the resource, including those inherited from the provider `default_tags` configuration block.

transitGatewayAttachmentId.description: The ID of the EC2 Transit Gateway Attachment to manage.

transitGatewayDefaultRouteTableAssociati.description: Boolean whether the VPC Attachment should be associated with the EC2 Transit Gateway association default route table. Default value: `true`.

transitGatewayDefaultRouteTablePropagati.description: Boolean whether the VPC Attachment should propagate routes with the EC2 Transit Gateway propagation default route table. Default value: `true`.
